{%- comment -%}
  Great Books article template.

  Turns a Great Books blog article (previously a bare H1 — a data record behind the
  Great Books Project table) into a real content page: eyebrow > H1 > work metadata
  (author / written / translation) > written body > "the edition I recommend" CTA >
  disclosure > related works from the same list.

  Heading hierarchy: H1 (work) > H2 (body sections, authored in the article content)
  > H2 (More from <list>) > H3 (related work titles).
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign gb_author = article.metafields.custom.author.value | default: article.metafields.custom.author -%}
{%- assign gb_written = article.metafields.custom.written_display.value
  | default: article.metafields.custom.written_display
-%}
{%- assign gb_translation = article.metafields.custom.translation.value
  | default: article.metafields.custom.translation
-%}
{%- assign gb_url = article.metafields.custom.affiliate_url.value | default: article.metafields.custom.affiliate_url -%}
{%- assign gb_list = article.metafields.custom.list_category.value
  | default: article.metafields.custom.list_category
  | default: 'Great Books'
-%}
{%- comment -%}
  Works written in English carry "Original" in the translation metafield. Blank it out so
  the page doesn't say "Original translation" — there is no translator to credit.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if gb_translation == 'Original' -%}{%- assign gb_translation = '' -%}{%- endif -%}

{%- comment -%}
  For works originally written in English the metafield names an editor/publisher, not a
  translator, so calling it a "translation" is wrong. The body itself tells us which case
  we're in: those pages carry a "Which edition to read" section instead.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign edition_word = 'translation' -%}
{%- if article.content contains 'Which edition to read' -%}
  {%- assign edition_word = 'edition' -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- assign gb_reading_time = article.metafields.custom.reading_time.value
  | default: article.metafields.custom.reading_time
-%}
{%- assign gb_difficulty = article.metafields.custom.difficulty.value | default: article.metafields.custom.difficulty -%}
{%- assign gb_language = article.metafields.custom.original_language.value
  | default: article.metafields.custom.original_language
-%}
{%- assign gb_genre = article.metafields.custom.genre.value | default: article.metafields.custom.genre -%}
{%- assign gb_period = article.metafields.custom.historical_period.value
  | default: article.metafields.custom.historical_period
-%}
{%- assign gb_best_for = article.metafields.custom.best_for.value | default: article.metafields.custom.best_for -%}
{%- assign gb_influenced_by = article.metafields.custom.influenced_by.value
  | default: article.metafields.custom.influenced_by
-%}
{%- assign gb_influenced = article.metafields.custom.influenced.value | default: article.metafields.custom.influenced -%}

{%- comment -%}
  ONE paginate pass computes everything that needs to walk the blog in reading order:
  the "Read next" cards (rendered near the bottom) and the single next work (shown in the
  Quick Facts box at the top). Doing it once avoids a second paginate tag in the same
  section, and Liquid `assign`s made inside a capture persist outside it.

  Reading order = ascending published_at (the synthetic dates assigned by orig_order at
  migration), so `| reverse` on Shopify's native descending order gives the list order.
  Paginate must wrap the loop DIRECTLY — inside a {% capture %} it is ignored and the
  silent 50-article cap comes back (this bit us: Odyssey was recommending Tocqueville).
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign passed_current = false -%}
{%- assign related_count = 0 -%}
{%- assign next_title = '' -%}
{%- assign next_url = '' -%}
{%- comment -%}
  Chronological position within this list ("No. 12 of 65"). Computed, never stored: insert a
  work into the list and every position downstream fixes itself.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign list_total = 0 -%}
{%- assign list_position = 0 -%}

{%- paginate blog.articles by 250 -%}
{%- assign reading_order = blog.articles | reverse -%}

{%- for other in reading_order -%}
  {%- assign other_list = other.metafields.custom.list_category.value
    | default: other.metafields.custom.list_category
  -%}
  {%- if other_list != gb_list -%}{%- continue -%}{%- endif -%}
  {%- assign list_total = list_total | plus: 1 -%}
  {%- if other.handle == article.handle -%}
    {%- assign list_position = list_total -%}
  {%- endif -%}
{%- endfor -%}

{%- capture related_items -%}
  {%- for pass in (1..2) -%}
    {%- for other in reading_order -%}
      {%- if related_count >= 3 -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
      {%- assign other_list = other.metafields.custom.list_category.value
        | default: other.metafields.custom.list_category
      -%}
      {%- if other_list != gb_list -%}{%- continue -%}{%- endif -%}
      {%- if other.handle == article.handle -%}
        {%- assign passed_current = true -%}
        {%- continue -%}
      {%- endif -%}
      {%- unless passed_current -%}{%- continue -%}{%- endunless -%}
      {%- assign related_count = related_count | plus: 1 -%}
      {%- if related_count == 1 -%}
        {%- assign next_title = other.title -%}
        {%- assign next_url = other.url -%}
      {%- endif -%}
      {%- assign other_author = other.metafields.custom.author.value | default: other.metafields.custom.author -%}
      {%- assign other_written = other.metafields.custom.written_display.value
        | default: other.metafields.custom.written_display
      -%}

      <li class="ra-gba__related-item">
        <h3 class="ra-gba__related-title">
          <a href="{{ other.url }}">{{ other.title }}</a>
        </h3>
        <span class="ra-gba__related-meta">
          {{- other_author -}}
          {%- if other_written != blank %} <span aria-hidden="true">·</span> {{ other_written }}{% endif -%}
        </span>
      </li>
    {%- endfor -%}
    {%- if related_count >= 3 -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
    {%- comment -%}Wrap: on the second pass, start collecting from the top of the list.{%- endcomment -%}
    {%- assign passed_current = true -%}
  {%- endfor -%}
{%- endcapture -%}
{%- endpaginate -%}

<article class="ra-section ra-gba">
  <div class="ra-container-md">
    <p class="ra-gba__eyebrow">
      <a href="{{ section.settings.parent_url }}">{{ section.settings.parent_label | escape }}</a>
      {%- if gb_list != blank %} <span aria-hidden="true">·</span> {{ gb_list }}{% endif -%}
    </p>

    <h1 class="ra-gba__title">{{ article.title }}</h1>

    <p class="ra-gba__meta">
      {%- if gb_author != blank -%}{{ gb_author }}{%- endif -%}
      {%- if gb_written != blank %} <span aria-hidden="true">·</span> Written {{ gb_written }}{% endif -%}
      {%- if gb_translation != blank %} <span aria-hidden="true">·</span> {{ gb_translation }} {{ edition_word }}{% endif -%}
    </p>

    {%- if article.excerpt != blank -%}
      <div class="ra-gba__lede">{{ article.excerpt }}</div>
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- comment -%}
      Cover of the recommended edition, beside the At a Glance box. The cover IS the link to
      the recommended edition, with a small text link under it — no button up here. The page
      is a reading guide, not a product listing: content first, one prominent CTA, at the end.

      Standing rule: the cover shown here must always be the exact edition recommended, and it
      links to that edition's affiliate URL.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="ra-gba__brief{% unless article.image %} ra-gba__brief--nocover{% endunless %}">
      {%- if article.image -%}
        <figure class="ra-gba__cover">
          {%- if gb_url != blank -%}
            <a href="{{ gb_url }}" target="_blank" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener">
              <img
                src="{{ article.image | image_url: width: 500 }}"
                alt="{{ article.image.alt | default: article.title | escape }}"
                loading="eager"
              >
            </a>
            <figcaption class="ra-gba__cover-link">
              <a href="{{ gb_url }}" target="_blank" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener">View on Amazon &rarr;</a>
            </figcaption>
          {%- else -%}
            <img
              src="{{ article.image | image_url: width: 500 }}"
              alt="{{ article.image.alt | default: article.title | escape }}"
              loading="eager"
            >
          {%- endif -%}
        </figure>
      {%- endif -%}

    {%- comment -%}
      Quick Facts — the whole page in one glance, above the fold. Each row renders only if
      its metafield has a value, so a work missing (say) a difficulty rating just drops
      that line rather than showing an empty label.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <aside class="ra-gba__facts" aria-label="At a glance">
      <p class="ra-gba__facts-title">At a Glance</p>
      <dl class="ra-gba__facts-list">
        {%- if gb_author != blank -%}
          <div class="ra-gba__fact"><dt>Author</dt><dd>{{ gb_author }}</dd></div>
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if gb_language != blank -%}
          <div class="ra-gba__fact"><dt>Original language</dt><dd>{{ gb_language }}</dd></div>
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if gb_written != blank -%}
          <div class="ra-gba__fact"><dt>Written</dt><dd>{{ gb_written }}</dd></div>
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if gb_genre != blank -%}
          <div class="ra-gba__fact"><dt>Genre</dt><dd>{{ gb_genre }}</dd></div>
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if gb_reading_time != blank -%}
          <div class="ra-gba__fact"><dt>Reading time</dt><dd>{{ gb_reading_time }}</dd></div>
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if gb_difficulty != blank -%}
          <div class="ra-gba__fact"><dt>Reading difficulty</dt><dd>{{ gb_difficulty }}</dd></div>
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if gb_period != blank -%}
          <div class="ra-gba__fact"><dt>Historical period</dt><dd>{{ gb_period }}</dd></div>
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if gb_best_for != blank -%}
          <div class="ra-gba__fact"><dt>Best for</dt><dd>{{ gb_best_for }}</dd></div>
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if gb_translation != blank -%}
          <div class="ra-gba__fact">
            <dt>Recommended {{ edition_word }}</dt>
            <dd>{{ gb_translation }}</dd>
          </div>
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if list_position > 0 -%}
          <div class="ra-gba__fact">
            <dt>Reading order</dt>
            <dd>
              No. {{ list_position }} of {{ list_total }} in {{ gb_list }}
              {%- if next_title != blank %} <span class="ra-gba__fact-next">Next: <a href="{{ next_url }}">{{ next_title }}</a></span>{% endif -%}
            </dd>
          </div>
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if gb_influenced_by != blank -%}
          <div class="ra-gba__fact"><dt>Influenced by</dt><dd>{{ gb_influenced_by }}</dd></div>
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if gb_influenced != blank -%}
          <div class="ra-gba__fact"><dt>Influenced</dt><dd>{{ gb_influenced }}</dd></div>
        {%- endif -%}
      </dl>
    </aside>
    </div>

    {%- comment -%}
      The guides carry a [[AMAZON]] marker at the end of the recommended edition's list item.
      Swap it for a small editorial text link — not a button. One inline link, in the place
      where a reader has just decided which edition they want.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- capture amazon_inline -%}
      <a class="ra-gba__inline-buy" href="{{ gb_url }}" target="_blank" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener">View on Amazon &rarr;</a>
    {%- endcapture -%}
    <div class="ra-gba__body rte">
      {%- if gb_url != blank -%}
        {{ article.content | replace: '[[AMAZON]]', amazon_inline }}
      {%- else -%}
        {{ article.content | replace: '[[AMAZON]]', '' }}
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>

    {%- comment -%}
      The ONE prominent call to action on the page, placed after the reader has finished the
      guide. Everything above it is editorial; nothing above it is a button.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- if gb_url != blank -%}
      <div class="ra-gba__actions">
        <a
          class="ra-button ra-button--primary"
          href="{{ gb_url }}"
          target="_blank"
          rel="nofollow sponsored noopener"
        >View on Amazon</a>
        {%- if gb_translation != blank -%}
          <span class="ra-gba__actions-note">The {{ gb_translation }} {{ edition_word }} — the edition recommended for this work.</span>
        {%- endif -%}
      </div>
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- comment -%}
      Collector's edition — renders ONLY when there's something real to show. The gate is
      `collector_label`: no label, no section. Nothing here degrades into an empty box or a
      placeholder on the ~100 works that will never have a collector's copy. Images, note,
      images, note and video are each independently optional, so a bare label + one photo
      works, and so does a full write-up with a video.

      No purchase link by design: these editions are mostly out of print or limited runs,
      so a "where I bought it" link would rot. The block documents the copy, it doesn't
      sell it.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- assign col_label = article.metafields.custom.collector_label.value
      | default: article.metafields.custom.collector_label
    -%}
    {%- if col_label != blank -%}
      {%- assign col_note = article.metafields.custom.collector_note.value
        | default: article.metafields.custom.collector_note
      -%}
      {%- assign col_video = article.metafields.custom.collector_video.value
        | default: article.metafields.custom.collector_video
      -%}
      {%- assign col_images = article.metafields.custom.collector_images.value -%}

      <section class="ra-gba__collector" aria-label="The edition I own">
        <p class="ra-gba__collector-eyebrow">{{ section.settings.collector_eyebrow | escape }}</p>
        <h2 class="ra-gba__collector-title">{{ col_label }}</h2>

        {%- if col_images != blank -%}
          <div class="ra-gba__collector-images">
            {%- for img in col_images -%}
              <figure class="ra-gba__collector-image">
                <img
                  src="{{ img | image_url: width: 900 }}"
                  alt="{{ img.alt | default: col_label | escape }} — {{ article.title | escape }}"
                  loading="lazy"
                >
              </figure>
            {%- endfor -%}
          </div>
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- if col_note != blank -%}
          <div class="ra-gba__collector-note">{{ col_note | newline_to_br }}</div>
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- if col_video != blank -%}
          {%- capture col_video_id -%}{%- render 'youtube-id', youtube_url: col_video -%}{%- endcapture -%}
          {%- assign col_video_id = col_video_id | strip -%}
          {%- if col_video_id != blank -%}
            <div class="ra-gba__collector-video">
              <iframe
                src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/{{ col_video_id }}"
                title="{{ col_label | escape }} — {{ article.title | escape }}"
                frameborder="0"
                allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
                allowfullscreen
              ></iframe>
            </div>
          {%- endif -%}
        {%- endif -%}

      </section>
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- if section.settings.disclosure != blank -%}
      <p class="ra-gba__disclosure">{{ section.settings.disclosure | escape }}</p>
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>

  {%- comment -%}
    "Read next" — rendered from the single paginate pass at the top of this section, which
    already walked the blog in reading order and captured these rows.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- if related_count > 0 -%}
    <div class="ra-container-md ra-gba__related">
      <h2 class="ra-gba__related-heading">Read next in {{ gb_list }}</h2>
      <ul class="ra-gba__related-list">{{ related_items }}</ul>
      <p class="ra-gba__back">
        <a class="ra-text-link" href="{{ section.settings.parent_url }}">Back to {{ section.settings.parent_label | escape }}</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  {%- endif -%}
</article>

{%- style -%}
  .ra-gba__eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 var(--ra-space-sm);
    font-size: var(--ra-text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ra-color-subtle);
  }

  .ra-gba__eyebrow a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .ra-gba__eyebrow a:hover {
    color: var(--ra-color-ink);
  }

  .ra-gba__title {
    margin: 0 0 var(--ra-space-xs);
    font-size: clamp(34px, 5.5vw, 52px);
    line-height: 1.06;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--ra-color-ink);
  }

  .ra-gba__meta {
    margin: 0 0 var(--ra-space-xl);
    font-size: var(--ra-text-sm);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: var(--ra-color-subtle);
  }

  .ra-gba__lede {
    margin-bottom: var(--ra-space-lg);
    font-size: 21px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ra-color-muted);
  }

  /* Cover + Quick Facts sit side by side; the cover column disappears on works with no
     cover on file, and the facts box takes the full width. */
  .ra-gba__brief {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr;
    gap: var(--ra-space-xl);
    align-items: start;
    margin: var(--ra-space-xl) 0 var(--ra-space-2xl);
  }

  .ra-gba__brief--nocover {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  .ra-gba__cover {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .ra-gba__cover-link {
    margin-top: var(--ra-space-sm);
    text-align: center;
    font-size: var(--ra-text-sm);
  }

  .ra-gba__cover-link a {
    color: var(--ra-color-subtle);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ra-color-border, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18));
    padding-bottom: 1px;
  }

  .ra-gba__cover-link a:hover {
    color: var(--ra-color-ink);
    border-color: var(--ra-color-ink);
  }

  /* Inline link on the recommended edition, inside the translation list. Deliberately quiet. */
  .ra-gba__inline-buy {
    white-space: nowrap;
    font-size: var(--ra-text-sm);
    color: var(--ra-color-subtle);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ra-color-border, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18));
  }

  .ra-gba__inline-buy:hover {
    color: var(--ra-color-ink);
    border-color: var(--ra-color-ink);
  }

  .ra-gba__cover img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 3px;
    box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25);
  }

  /* Quick Facts */
  .ra-gba__facts {
    margin: 0;
    padding: var(--ra-space-lg) var(--ra-space-xl);
    border: 1px solid var(--ra-color-border, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.14));
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--ra-color-soft, #f7f7f5);
  }

  .ra-gba__facts-title {
    margin: 0 0 var(--ra-space-md);
    font-size: var(--ra-text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ra-color-subtle);
  }

  .ra-gba__facts-list {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .ra-gba__fact {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 190px 1fr;
    gap: var(--ra-space-md);
    padding: 9px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ra-color-border, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1));
  }

  .ra-gba__fact:first-child {
    border-top: 0;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .ra-gba__fact dt {
    margin: 0;
    align-self: center;
    font-size: var(--ra-text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ra-color-subtle);
  }

  .ra-gba__fact dd {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--ra-color-ink);
  }

  .ra-gba__fact-next {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 2px;
    font-size: var(--ra-text-sm);
    color: var(--ra-color-subtle);
  }

  .ra-gba__fact dd a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--ra-color-border);
  }

  .ra-gba__fact dd a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: var(--ra-color-ink);
  }

  /* Collector's edition — only renders when the collector_label metafield is set */
  .ra-gba__collector {
    margin-top: var(--ra-space-4xl);
    padding-top: var(--ra-space-xl);
    border-top: 2px solid var(--ra-color-ink);
  }

  .ra-gba__collector-eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 var(--ra-space-xs);
    font-size: var(--ra-text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ra-color-subtle);
  }

  .ra-gba__collector-title {
    margin: 0 0 var(--ra-space-lg);
    font-size: 28px;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--ra-color-ink);
  }

  .ra-gba__collector-images {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--ra-space-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--ra-space-lg);
  }

  .ra-gba__collector-image {
    margin: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--ra-color-soft);
  }

  .ra-gba__collector-image img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .ra-gba__collector-note {
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ra-color-muted);
  }

  .ra-gba__collector-video {
    position: relative;
    margin-top: var(--ra-space-lg);
    padding-bottom: 56.25%;
    height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .ra-gba__collector-video iframe {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
  }

  @media screen and (max-width: 749px) {
    .ra-gba__brief {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      justify-items: center;
    }

    .ra-gba__cover {
      max-width: 150px;
    }

    .ra-gba__facts {
      width: 100%;
      padding: var(--ra-space-md) var(--ra-space-lg);
    }

    .ra-gba__fact {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2px;
    }
  }

  .ra-gba__body h2 {
    margin: var(--ra-space-xl) 0 var(--ra-space-sm);
    font-size: 26px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--ra-color-ink);
  }

  .ra-gba__body p,
  .ra-gba__body li {
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ra-color-muted);
  }

  .ra-gba__body blockquote {
    margin: var(--ra-space-lg) 0;
    padding-left: var(--ra-space-lg);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--ra-color-border, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15));
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .ra-gba__actions {
    margin-top: var(--ra-space-2xl);
  }

  .ra-gba__actions-note {
    display: block;
    margin-top: var(--ra-space-sm);
    font-size: var(--ra-text-sm);
    color: var(--ra-color-subtle);
  }

  .ra-gba__disclosure {
    margin-top: var(--ra-space-xl);
    padding-top: var(--ra-space-md);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ra-color-border, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1));
    font-size: var(--ra-text-sm);
    color: var(--ra-color-subtle);
  }

  .ra-gba__related {
    margin-top: var(--ra-space-4xl);
  }

  .ra-gba__related-heading {
    margin: 0 0 var(--ra-space-lg);
    font-size: 26px;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--ra-color-ink);
  }

  .ra-gba__related-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .ra-gba__related-item {
    padding: var(--ra-space-md) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ra-color-border, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1));
  }

  .ra-gba__related-title {
    margin: 0 0 4px;
    font-size: 21px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .ra-gba__related-title a {
    color: var(--ra-color-ink);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .ra-gba__related-title a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .ra-gba__related-meta {
    font-size: var(--ra-text-sm);
    color: var(--ra-color-subtle);
  }

  .ra-gba__back {
    margin-top: var(--ra-space-xl);
  }
{%- endstyle -%}

